In this letter, President Barack Obama informs the Speaker of the House of Representatives and the President pro tempore of the Senate about the military operations in Iraq against the Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant (ISIL). He describes the series of operations that have been conducted, including airstrikes, support for Iraqi forces, and humanitarian assistance. The President states that he has ordered the deployment of additional U.S. Armed Forces personnel to Iraq and the use of airstrikes and other necessary actions to degrade and defeat ISIL. He emphasizes that these actions are being undertaken in coordination with the Government of Iraq and coalition partners. The President asserts his constitutional and statutory authority as Commander in Chief and Chief Executive to carry out these actions and to conduct foreign relations. He provides this report to keep the Congress informed in accordance with the War Powers Resolution.